  "body": "**Description**\r\n\r\ncontainerd build fails with Go version below 1.13. The documentation states \"Go 1.10.x or above\" as dependecy, but for me it failed with 1.12. After upgrading my Go to 1.13, it built successfully. Looks like documentation needs to be updated for this dependency. It should state:\r\n\"Go 1.13.x or above\"\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the issue:**\r\n1. Use a Go version lower than 1.13, higher than 1.10 (currently documented lower limit)\r\n2. Download containerd : go get github.com/containerd/containerd\r\n3. Build using make : make\r\n\r\n**Describe the results you received:**\r\nIt builds /bin/ctr properly. After that during build of /bin/containerd it fails with a few messages pointing to the same problem.\r\nundefined: \"github.com/containerd/containerd/vendor/github.com/pkg/errors\".Is\r\n\r\n**Describe the results you expected:**\r\nSuccessful build\r\n\r\n$ make\r\n+ bin/ctr\r\n+ bin/containerd\r\n+ bin/containerd-stress\r\n+ bin/containerd-shim\r\n+ bin/containerd-shim-runc-v1\r\n+ bin/containerd-shim-runc-v2\r\n+ binaries\r\n\r\n\r\n**Output of `containerd --version`:**\r\n\r\n```\r\nN/A . Problem happening during build. Pulled master branch using go get.\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Any other relevant information:**\r\nIt looks like the build depends on the Errors.Is function which is in the https://github.com/pkg/errors/blob/master/go113.go file. \r\nAfter failed attempts to build containerd with Go 1.12, I upgraded to Go to 1.13 and build completed successfully.",
